42:
Ahaz fathered Jarah;
Jarah fathered Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri;
Zimri fathered Moza.

2:
They were archers who could use either the right or left hand, both to sling stones and shoot arrows from a bow.
 They were Saul’s relatives
 from Benjamin:

3:
Their chief was Ahiezer son of Shemaah the Gibeathite.
Then there was his brother Joash;
Jeziel and Pelet sons of Azmaveth;
Beracah, Jehu the Anathothite;

5:
So David assembled all Israel,
 from the Shihor of Egypt to the entrance of Hamath,
 to bring the ark of God from Kiriath-jearim.

15:
Joab
 son of Zeruiah was over the army;
Jehoshaphat son of Ahilud was court historian;

16:
Zadok son of Ahitub and Ahimelech
 son of Abiathar were priests;
Shavsha was court secretary;

17:
Benaiah son of Jehoiada
 was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites;
and David’s sons were the chief officials at the king’s side.

9:
But a son will be born to you; he will be a man of rest. I will give him rest from all his surrounding enemies,
 for his name will be Solomon,
 and I will give peace and quiet to Israel during his reign.

20:
As for the rest of Levi’s sons:
from Amram’s sons: Shubael;
from Shubael’s sons: Jehdeiah.

